577			log("\n");
578			log("Map internal flip-flop cells to the flip-flop cells in the technology\n");
579			log("library specified in the given liberty files.\n");
580			log("\n");
581			log("This pass may add inverters as needed. Therefore it is recommended to\n");
582			log("first run this pass and then map the logic paths to the target technology.\n");
583			log("\n");
584			log("When called with -prepare, this command will convert the internal FF cells\n");
585			log("to the internal cell types that best match the cells found in the given\n");
586			log("liberty file, but won't actually map them to the target cells.\n");
587			log("\n");
588			log("When called with -map-only, this command will only map internal cell\n");
589			log("types that are already of exactly the right type to match the target\n");
590			log("cells, leaving remaining internal cells untouched.\n");
591			log("\n");
592			log("When called with -info, this command will only print the target cell\n");
593			log("list, along with their associated internal cell types, and the arguments\n");
594			log("that would be passed to the dfflegalize pass.  The design will not be\n");
595			log("changed.\n");
596			log("\n");
597			log("When called with -dont_use, this command will not map to the specified cell\n");
598			log("name as an alternative to setting the dont_use property in the Liberty file.\n");
599			log("This argument can be called multiple times with different cell names. This\n");
600			log("argument also supports simple glob patterns in the cell name.\n");
